article.headline: Eastern Illinois 63, Wisconsin-Green Bay 61
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. (AP) -- Romain Martin made a layup with 30 seconds to go as Eastern Illinois eked out a 63-61 victory over Wisconsin-Green Bay on Tuesday night. The game remained close throughout, with 13 lead changes and neither team ever pulling ahead by more than six points. It was tied 10 times. The Panthers (2-4), who went into halftime with a 33-28 edge, were led in scoring by Mike Robinson, who had 16. Bobby Catchings added 15 and Martin finished with 13. Ryan Evanochko lead the Phoenix (1-3) scoring with a game-high 19 points in 38 minutes on the floor. He was 8-of-10 from the foul line and led all players with five assists. Two other players finished in double figures for Wisconsin-Green Bay. Troy Cotton had 15 points and Mike Schachtner added 12 more for the Phoenix.
